description: Data recored from a single web-services methods.

sessionId.description: The distinct ID assigned to this call.

timestamp.description: The timestamp of the request, in UTC milliseconds

userId.description: The ID of the user making the calls

userAgent.description: Identifies the software agent that made the call. Extracted from the User-Agent header

host.description: The domain name of the server (for virtual hosting), and the TCP port number on which the server is listening

origin.description: Initiates a request for cross-origin resource sharing (asks server for an 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' response header)

xForwardedFor.description: The X-Forwarded-For (XFF) HTTP header field is a de facto standard for identifying the originating IP address of a client connecting to a web server through an HTTP proxy or load balancer.

via.description: Informs the server of proxies through which the request was sent

threadId.description: The ID of the thread that accepted this call

elapseMS.description: The elapse time in MS for the call

success.description: Did the call complete without an error?

stack.description: This string identifies the stack where the request originated

instance.description: This string identifies the stack instance where the request originated.  This is used for partitioning.

date.description: This string identifies the stack instance where the request originated. This is used for partitioning.

vmId.description: The VMID of the JVM that processed this request. A VMID is a identifier that is unique across all Java virtual machines.

returnObjectId.description: The ID of the returned object when it exits.

queryString.description: The query string of the request.

oauthClientId.description: The ID of the OAuth Client making the request

basicAuthUsername.description: The username used in the authorization header of the request, if the request used basic authentication.
